/div>            </td>            <td colspan="2">            <div align="center">250</div>            </td>        </tr>        <tr>            <td>Масса собственно дробилки, т</td>            <td>            <div align="center">48,5</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">48,5</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">87,5</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">88</div>            </td>        </tr>    </tbody></table>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="1">    <tbody>        <tr>            <td width="43%">            <div align="center"><b>Параметры</b></div>            </td>            <td width="16%">            <div align="center"><b>КМД 1750Гр</b></div>            </td>            <td width="13%">            <div align="center"><b>КМД 1750Т</b></div>            </td>            <td width="14%">            <div align="center"><b>КМД 2200Гр</b></div>            </td>            <td width="14%">            <div align="center"><b>КМД 2200Т</b></div>            </td>        </tr>        <tr>            <td>Ширина приемной щели, мм</td>            <td>            <div align="center">130</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">80</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">140</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">100</div>            </td>        </tr>        <tr>            <td>Наибольший размер кусков питания, мм</td>            <td>            <div align="center">100</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">70</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">110</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">85</div>            </td>        </tr>        <tr>            <td>Ширина разгрузочной щели, мм</td>            <td>            <div align="center">9...20</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">5...15</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">10...20</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">5...15</div>            </td>        </tr>        <tr>            <td>Диаметр основания дробящего конуса, мм</td>            <td colspan="2">            <div align="center">1750</div>            </td>            <td colspan="2">            <div align="center">2200</div>            </td>        </tr>        <tr>            <td>Производительность при дроблении кристаллических материалов средней крепости с влагосодержанием до 4% в открытом цикле, м3/ч, не менее</td>            <td>           <div align="center">95...230</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">85...110</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">220...260</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">160...220</div>            </td>        </tr>        <tr>            <td>Мощность приводного электродвигателя, кВт</td>            <td colspan="2">           <div align="center">160</div>            </td>            <td colspan="2">            <div align="center">250</div>            </td>        </tr>        <tr>            <td>Масса собственно дробилки, т</td>            <td>            <div align="center">48</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">48</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">88</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">88</div>            </td>        </tr>    </tbody></table>\r\n\r\n<p>The gyratory crusher is the continuous operation machine used for crushing the ore and no ore minerals by grinding the material inside of fixed tapered bowl with the cone which is making the rotating swing (gyration motion). The crushing process and discharge under the gyratory crusher operation are noninterruptible, and there is not an idle run. The gyratory inertial crushers KMD are not used for crushing the plastic materials. The gyratory crushers KSD and KMD with the spring damping and mechanized regulating of opening are designated for operating under ultimate strength up to 4%. The gyratory crushers are manufactured in two versions: Gr – coarse crushing, T – fine crushing. The construction of the gyratory crusher KSD is very similar to the gyratory crusher KMD, they differ from each other only by the embodiment of some assembly units. The assembly units and parts of the gyratory crushers are maximally unified. The productivity of the gyratory crusher for grinding the crystalline materials of intermediate hardness and moisture up to 4% is 85 – 610 m3/hour in the open cycle; and the electric motor power is up to 250 kW. The machine mass without components and spare parts is 48 – 88 tons.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">The crushers KST and KDT 1750 and 2200 are designated for grinding the ore and no ore minerals and analogical materials (except to plastic ones). It is permitted to use crushers KSD and KMD to grind the materials having the strength properties (fineness and crushability) which are higher than those of the most difficultly crushed ores, such as ferrochromium. Generally, the maximum permissible stress of compression for crushed material shall not exceed 300 MPa (3000 kg/mm2). The clumping rocks shall be flushed before crushing, and the fine fractions in the feeding shall be screened and removed for increasing the productivity of the crusher and for decreasing the wear of surface armor and the power consumption. The crushing spaces of the crusher are designed to enable the crusher application in sequential technological processes. Additionally, each the type of crushers can have an independent designation related to the final product of crushing. The crushing practice shows materials and ores which have the best and worst relative results. However, the structure of crusher enables to regulate the discharging opening for obtaining the product parameters close to the required characteristics. If the processed ore is the very difficulty crushed one, using the 6 mm opening provides less than two openings up to 69% according to the curve 2. In this case, to get 90% of the class minus 12 mm, the closed cycle of crusher operation is made with the control screening cycle and the product is classified as the class minus 12 mm.</p>', '<p>Серіппелі амортизациялық және механикаландырылып реттелетін саңылаулары бар КСД және КМД конусты уақтағыштары және кентас пен кентас емес пайдалы қазбаларды және оларға ұқсас (пластикалықтан басқа) уақытша қарсыластығы 4% дейінгі материалдарды уақтауға арналған. Конусты кмд уақтағышының екі түрі бар: Гр – ірі уақтау, Т – жіңішке уақтау. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>КСД және КМД уақтағыштары өзінің құрылымы бойынша бір-біріне анағұрлым жақын және жекелеп құрастырылған бірліктерінің сындарлы орындалуымен ғана айрықшаланады. Жинақтау бірліктері мен уақтағыш бөлшектері максималды түрде сәйкестендірілген.</p> \r\n\r\n<p><b>ТЕХНИКАЛЫҚ СИПАТТАМАСЫ</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="1">    <tbody>        <tr>            <td width="43%">            <div align="center"><b>Параметры</b></div>            </td>            <td width="16%">            <div align="center"><b>КСД 1750Гр</b></div>            </td>            <td width="13%">            <div align="center"><b>КСД 1750Т</b></div>            </td>            <td width="14%">            <div align="center"><b>КСД 2200Гр</b></div>            </td>            <td width="14%">            <div align="center"><b>КСД 2200Т</b></div>            </td>        </tr>        <tr>            <td>Ширина приемной щели, мм</td>            <td>            <div align="center">250</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">200</div>            </td>            <td>            <div align="center">350</div>            </td>            <td>  